==English==
=== Etymology ===
From German ''prūme'', originally from the Latin ''prunum'', from the Greek ''prounon'', a variant form of ''proumnon'' meaning '''[[plum]]'''.

===Pronunciation===
*[[w:AHD|AHD]]: plŭm
*[[w:IPA|IPA]]: /plʌm/
*[[w:SAMPA|SAMPA]]: /<tt>plVm</tt>/

====Homophones====
*[[plumb]]

===Noun===
'''plum''' (''plural'' '''[[plums]]''')

#(''also'' '''plum tree''') A [[stone-fruit]] tree of the ''[[Prunus]]'' family.
#The [[fruit]] of the plum tree.
#(colour) A dark [[bluish]]-[[red]] [[color]]/[[colour]], the colour of some plums.
#:<table><tr><td>plum colour: &nbsp;</td><td bgcolor="#5F4951" width="80">&nbsp; </td></tr></table>
#A desirable thing.
#A [[raisin]], when used in a pudding or cake.
#(''slang''; ''usually in plural'') A [[testicle]].


